/* Ensure secondary popup content expands with popup window */
.k-window.scparts-popup-style .k-window-content,
.k-window.scparts-popup-style .form-container {
    width: 100% !important;   /* Fill full popup width */
    height: 100% !important;  /* Fill full popup height */
    box-sizing: border-box;   /* Include padding in size calculation */
    overflow: auto;           /* Allow scroll if content is too big */
}
ðŸ”‘ What this does
.k-window-content â†’ ensures the built-in Kendo content container expands.

.form-container â†’ ensures your custom content container also stretches to fit.

Now when you change .k-window.scparts-popup-style { width: 60vw; height: 90vh; }, the Part Information and Supplier Information sections will expand/contract with it.

âš¡ Extra Tip
If you want the sections inside (.form-row, .form-group) to also stretch proportionally, make sure they use % or flex rather than fixed widths. Example:

css
Copy code
.form-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 12px;
    width: 100%;   /* Ensure row stretches with container */
}
.form-group {
    flex: 1;       /* Each group takes equal share of row */
    min-width: 200px; /* Prevent collapsing too small */
}
